record.title: BLI measurement of hemoglobin serum elements

entities_of_interest.name: Human serum
entities_of_interest.description: Blood was drawn after 12 hours of fasting

preparation_protocol.name: Centrifugation
preparation_protocol.description: Tubes were centrifuged for 10 min at 1,300g at 4°C within 2 hours of collection

preparation_protocol.name: Aliquotation
preparation_protocol.description: The supernatant was distributed among 0.5mL cryostorage tubes that were maintained at 4°C

storage_preparation.name: Flash freezing in liquid nitrogen
storage_preparation.description: Aliquotes were placed in liquid nitrogen for 5 min

derived_parameters.name: KD of hemoglobin to unknown component in serum

plates.name: Sample plate
plates.type: Solid Black Flat Bottom Polystyrene TC-treated Microplates
